# 3. 出発！美味しいカレーにご案内

Ichika: Seeing all those rows of books at the History Archive Museum was pretty amazing. It was also helpful that there were photos included with the documents they had on display.
Haruka: And the building itself was very beautiful. I think that kind of architecture is referred to as “retro-modern”.
Ichika: It did have its own presence. Saki was freaking out and yelling “this place is so pretty!”
Saki: What?! I wasn't freaking out! I was just regular excited—
Saki: Whoa! Oh my gosh, look! The water! The seagulls are playing together!
Haruka: Hehe, and history repeats itself.
Haruka: But I understand how freeing this feels. The smell of the sea is also very refreshing.
Classmate: Hey, Kiritani. I've been wondering for a while, but are those glasses...supposed to be a disguise?
Haruka: Oh, yes. I don't usually wear a pair, but since I'm here with all of you today, I wouldn't want to cause a ruckus because of a fan spotting me.
Classmate: Y-You...really are a star!
Classmate: But, I do see a lot of pictures taken of celebrities I like uploaded onto social media. I guess celebrities have it tough, huh?
Haruka: Well... It can be tough, but fans show their support in different ways, and that support always makes me happy.
Classmate: Wow... You really do think about your fans, Kiritani!
Teacher: And I think that's enough chatter for the time being.
Teacher: Alright, you will now have free time. Please assemble into your groups before heading off.
Teacher: I will be doing a roll call before dismissing you home, so please be at the station by 5 p.m. sharp. If there are any problems, contact me immediately.
Saki: Understood!
Teacher: Hehe, I like your attitude, Tenma.
Teacher: Alright everyone, do not forget that you are all representatives of Miyamasuzaka Girls Academy. But at the same time, go have fun and enjoy yourselves.
Students: Understood!
Saki: Okie dokie, everybody! Off we go!
Haruka: I think we have the ship tour first on our itinerary.
Saki: Yup! I know the view from the deck is supposed to be really nice, but I can't wait to see the captain's cabin and stuff either!
Haruka: I feel the same way. We should make the most of this opportunity, so let's take our time looking around.
Ichika: Wow, I didn't realize how large a ship's deck is.
Haruka: Just like the guidebook said, the view from here is really beautiful. You get to see the city and the water, and pretty far out on a sunny day like this.
Saki: Oh, there's a tower over there! I bet we could get an even better look from the top of that! You think we'd be able to see the Ferris wheel across the way?
Saki: Apparently this ship was used to host parties and stuff before. I wonder if this is what celebrities did to have fun.
Inoue: I'm sure they did! I bet they were thinking how nice the sea breeze felt when they were up here...
Inoue: Oh, the wind's getting a little stronger... Whoa!
Ichika: Ah! Inoue!
Haruka: Inoue, are you alright?
Inoue: Y-Yeah...
Haruka: Please be careful. It would be awful if you hurt yourself.
Inoue: O-Of course. I'm ever so grateful for you saving me...
Ichika: Huh? Why are you talking like that?
Sonoda: She's probably just smitten by Kiritani's idol aura, no?
Inoue: I-It's not like I can help it! I mean, there's no way anyone could resist that!
Haruka: Um... It's a little embarrassing when you put it like that...
Haruka: Anyway, we've had a look around inside the ship, so shall we head over for lunch? I'm starting to feel a little hungry.
Saki: Me too, me too! I feel like it's only a matter of seconds before my stomach growls.
Haruka: Hehe, then we'd better hurry.
Saki: Wow! So this is the curry place you talked about, Haruka?!
Ichika: The terrace seating really adds to the atmosphere. It looks even better in real life than in the photos.
Haruka: Hehe, it's beautiful, isn't it? Looks like they aren't that busy right now, so we should be able to get a table.
Saki: Let's hurry up and go in! I'm starving!
Sonoda: Wow, even the interior is really pretty!
Ichika: They have a lot of things on the menu too. This lunch special that comes with Salisbury steak looks really good.
Saki: You came here for work before, right, Haruka? What did you order back then?
Haruka: I had the chicken curry lunch special. At the time, I ordered it with rice, but maybe I'll go with naan this time.
Ichika: Oh, you'll be ordering the chicken curry again? I guess it's just that good, huh.
Saki: Oh no, everything looks so yummy that I can't choose! I think I'm leaning towards this green curry...
Haruka: I heard that's really spicy, so maybe be careful.
Saki: What?
Haruka: Another performer who was at the shoot with me had that, and it was so spicy that they fainted from the pain. That curry is apparently quite infamous.
Saki: I didn't know that! Wow, dodged a bullet there... Huh?
Saki: Oh, OH MY GOSH!
Ichika: Wh-What's wrong, Saki?!
Saki: Look! Look over there!
Sonoda: That's...
Saki: That's Haruka's autograph!
Haruka: Huh?
Inoue: Wow, it is!
Ichika: Amazing... Haruka really is famous...
Haruka: Could you all please stop staring at it? Besides, that's from back when I was in ASRUN.
Haruka: Also, we should probably order soon so this doesn't eat into our schedule.
Saki: You got it! Alright, I think I'll order...
Saki: Yummm!!!
Saki: The guidebook did say it was authentic, but the spiciness makes it so delicious! I think I'm starting to feel kinda hot...!
Ichika: Haha. I'm glad that the chicken curry isn't so spicy. I went with rice, but the naan looks really good too.
Haruka: Yes, it's very nice and freshly made too. It's so soft and chewy, I feel like I could eat a whole lot of it.
Saki: *Sigh* We get to see fun and interesting things, eat delicious foods...I'm so happy. If only we could have field trips every day...
Sonoda: I don't know if that's a good idea.
Inoue: But I totally get how you feel! Speaking of which, don't we get to go on a school trip next year? I can't wait!
Ichika: Where do you think we'll get to go for our school trip? Hokkaido? Or maybe Okinawa?
Saki: Some of the second-years in my club were saying that they're going to Kyoto. Right?
Inoue: Oh yeah, they did say that. But I'd rather go to Okinawa.
Haruka: Well, I think it might change when it's our turn. A second-year I know told me that they went to PXL for their field trip.
Saki: Oh, true! Then I guess we'll just have to wait and see where we get to go for our school trip!
Saki: I hope we get to be in the same group again!
Haruka: In the same group...
Inoue: But we might not be in the same class next year, and then wouldn't we only see each other when everyone gathers?
Saki: I guess that could happen... But if we're lucky, we might all end up in the same class again!
Sonoda: I think there's a limit to luck, though.
Ichika: Hehe, I think so too.
Ichika: Kiritani, are you okay?
Haruka: Oh, yes. It's nothing to worry about.
Haruka: The curry I got was just spicier than I expected.
Haruka: I guess since everyone's done, shall we head out?
Saki: Let's!
Saki: Wow, it's way bigger than I thought! So this is the Red Brick Center!
Haruka: It looks pretty retro, or like a building you'd see in another country. The shops inside are supposed to be just as classy as the exterior, right?
Sonoda: I think so. I'm pretty sure the guidebook said that there's a Building 1 and a Building 2, but... Is the bigger one Building 1?
Haruka: Actually, it looks like the smaller one is Building 1. Shall we head over there first?
Ichika: Oh, I just remembered. Would it be alright if I went to buy some souvenirs?
Ichika: Since we're already here, I was hoping to get some while we still have time.
Inoue: Yeah, sounds good. I was thinking the same thing!
Saki: Okie dokie! First stop is the souvenir shops, then! Let's go♪
